Create Entities from Existing Database - Symfony

Follow the steps below :-

1. Create a directory 'doctrine' inside /src/SalonSolutions/WebBundle/Resources/Config/

2. Run the following commands on terminal :-

AdminBundle

1) php app/console doctrine:mapping:import --force SalonSolutionAdminBundle xml

2) php app/console doctrine:mapping:convert annotation ./src

3) php app/console doctrine:generate:entities SalonSolutionAdminBundle


WebBundle

1) php app/console doctrine:mapping:import --force SalonSolutionWebBundle xml

2) php app/console doctrine:mapping:convert annotation ./src

3) php app/console doctrine:generate:entities SalonSolutionWebBundle


SalonBundle

1) php app/console doctrine:mapping:import --force SalonSolutionSalonBundle xml

2) php app/console doctrine:mapping:convert annotation ./src

3) php app/console doctrine:generate:entities SalonSolutionSalonBundle



EmployeeBundle

1) php app/console doctrine:mapping:import --force SalonSolutionEmployeeBundle xml

2) php app/console doctrine:mapping:convert annotation ./src

3) php app/console doctrine:generate:entities SalonSolutionEmployeeBundle
